io.amelia.data.parcel

Class ParcelCarrier

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.amelia.data.parcel.ParcelCarrier

  • public class ParcelCarrier
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines a carrier containing data and signals to be transmitted over network, IPC, and by reference. A ParcelSender is the origin of the carrier, while ParcelReceiver is the target of the carrier.

    The best way to get one of these is to call obtain() method, which will pull from a pool of recycled objects.

      • setPayload

        public void setPayload(@Nonnull
                       java.lang.Object payload)
        Sets the payload to be transmitted with this carrier.

        Note: Be advised that objects that don't implement Parcel or isn't annotated as being Parcelable, usually can't be transmittable over the network. So it's best practice to use Parcel whenever possible. Ultimately, it's up to the network implementation if the payload is acceptable.

        Parameters:
        payload - The payload to set on this carrier.
